log(p/(1-p)) = ğ›½_0 + ğ›½_1 x X_1 + ğ›½_2 x X_2 ... + ğ›½_n x X_n
 
Solving for probability:

ğ‘ = 1 / ( 1 + e^( ğ›½_0 + ğ›½_1 x X_1 + ğ›½_2 x X_2 ... + ğ›½_n x X_n )
 
This formula enables individual risk prediction based on personal characteristics such as habits, age, or genetics â€” highly useful in epidemiology, personalized medicine, and public health.
